name: All in Good Time
text: When you set this scheme in motion, take an extra turn after this one. Schemes can't be set in motion that turn.
flavor: "Take a moment. Ponder the depths of your insignificance."

name: Leonin Abunas
text: Artifacts you control have hexproof. (They can't be the targets of spells or abilities your opponents control.)
flavor: Only leonin clerics who can survive the Razor Fields for one turning of the suns can stand in the Cave of Light.

name: All Shall Smolder in My Wake
text: When you set this scheme in motion, destroy up to one target artifact, up to one target enchantment, and up to one target nonbasic land.
flavor: "It's my goal to find the melting point of every substance."

name: Metallurgeon
text: {W}, {T}: Regenerate target artifact.
flavor: "By the time I got there, the heart had stopped. Fortunately, I was able to replace it with something better."

name: Approach My Molten Realm
text: When you set this scheme in motion, until your next turn, if a source would deal damage, it deals double that damage instead.
flavor: "It's a dragon-infested lavascape of notorious peril. Make yourselves at home."

name: Oblivion Ring
text: When Oblivion Ring enters the battlefield, exile another target nonland permanent.\nWhen Oblivion Ring leaves the battlefield, return the exiled card to the battlefield under its owner's control.

name: Behold the Power of Destruction
text: When you set this scheme in motion, destroy all nonland permanents target opponent controls.
flavor: "I'd call that a successful first test. Golem! Rearm the Doom Citadel!"

name: Path to Exile
text: Exile target creature. Its controller may search his or her library for a basic land card, put that card onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle his or her library.

name: Choose Your Champion
text: When you set this scheme in motion, target opponent chooses a player. Until your next turn, only you and the chosen player can cast spells and attack with creatures.
flavor: "It seems the fate of the world rests on your shoulders, feeble child."

name: Sanctum Gargoyle
text: Flying\nWhen Sanctum Gargoyle enters the battlefield, you may return target artifact card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: As their supplies of etherium dwindled, mechanists sent gargoyles farther and farther afield in search of salvage.

name: Dance, Pathetic Marionette
text: When you set this scheme in motion, each opponent reveals cards from the top of his or her library until he or she reveals a creature card. Choose one of the revealed creature cards and put it onto the battlefield under your control. Put all other cards revealed this way into their owners' graveyards.

name: March of the Machines
text: Each noncreature artifact is an artifact creature with power and toughness each equal to its converted mana cost. (Equipment that's a creature can't equip a creature.)

name: The Dead Shall Serve
text: When you set this scheme in motion, for each opponent, put up to one target creature card from that player's graveyard onto the battlefield under your control. Each of those creatures attacks its owner each combat if able.
flavor: "Tell your old master I said hello."

name: Master Transmuter
text: {U}, {T}, Return an artifact you control to its owner's hand: You may put an artifact card from your hand onto the battlefield.
flavor: "Wasted potential surrounds us. Lend me that bauble, and let me see what it can be made to be."

name: A Display of My Dark Power
text: When you set this scheme in motion, until your next turn, whenever a player taps a land for mana, that player adds one mana to his or her mana pool of any type that land produced.
flavor: "What would you say is my greatest attribute? Is it my gluttonous lust for power?"

name: Spin into Myth
text: Put target creature on top of its owner's library, then fateseal 2. (To fateseal 2, look at the top two cards of an opponent's library, then put any number of them on the bottom of that player's library and the rest on top in any order.)

name: Embrace My Diabolical Vision
text: When you set this scheme in motion, each player shuffles his or her hand and graveyard into his or her library. You draw seven cards, then each other player draws four cards.
flavor: "My vision is for the good of everyone. Mostly me."

name: Avatar of Woe
text: If there are ten or more creature cards total in all graveyards, Avatar of Woe costs {6} less to cast.\nFear (This creature can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)\n{T}: Destroy target creature. It can't be regenerated.

name: Every Hope Shall Vanish
text: When you set this scheme in motion, each opponent reveals his or her hand. Choose a nonland card from each of those hands. Those players discard those cards.
flavor: "Oh, I think I will get away with this."

name: Beacon of Unrest
text: Put target artifact or creature card from a graveyard onto the battlefield under your control. Shuffle Beacon of Unrest into its owner's library.
flavor: A vertical scream pierces the night air and echoes doom through the clouds.

name: Every Last Vestige Shall Rot
text: When you set this scheme in motion, you may pay {X}. If you do, put each nonland permanent target player controls with converted mana cost X or less on the bottom of its owner's library.
flavor: "May bloodberries grow from your remains."

name: Bog Witch
text: {B}, {T}, Discard a card: Add {B}{B}{B} to your mana pool.
flavor: The world is the body. The mana is the blood. The witch is the surgeon.

name: Evil Comes to Fruition
text: When you set this scheme in motion, put seven 0/1 green Plant creature tokens onto the battlefield. If you control ten or more lands, put seven 3/3 green Elemental creature tokens onto the battlefield instead.
flavor: "The plants justify the means."

name: Cemetery Reaper
text: Other Zombie creatures you control get +1/+1.\n{2}{B}, {T}: Exile target creature card from a graveyard. Put a 2/2 black Zombie creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: Every grave cradles a recruit.

name: The Fate of the Flammable
text: When you set this scheme in motion, target opponent chooses self or others. If that player chooses self, this scheme deals 6 damage to him or her. If the player chooses others, this scheme deals 3 damage to each of your other opponents.

name: Corpse Connoisseur
text: When Corpse Connoisseur enters the battlefield, you may search your library for a creature card and put that card into your graveyard. If you do, shuffle your library.\nUnearth {3}{B} ({3}{B}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)

name: Feed the Machine
text: When you set this scheme in motion, target opponent chooses self or others. If that player chooses self, he or she sacrifices two creatures. If the player chooses others, each of your other opponents sacrifices a creature.
flavor: "Even you have a purpose. Your blood will oil the gears."

name: Dregscape Zombie
text: Unearth {B} ({B}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)
flavor: The undead of Grixis are fueled by their hatred of the living.

name: I Bask in Your Silent Awe
text: (An ongoing scheme remains face up until it's abandoned.)\nEach opponent can't cast more than one spell each turn.\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, if no opponent cast a spell since your last turn ended, abandon this scheme.

name: Extractor Demon
text: Flying\nWhenever another creature leaves the battlefield, you may have target player put the top two cards of his or her library into his or her graveyard.\nUnearth {2}{B} ({2}{B}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)

name: I Call on the Ancient Magics
text: When you set this scheme in motion, each other player searches his or her library for a card, reveals it, and puts it into his or her hand. Then you search your library for two cards and put them into your hand. Each player shuffles his or her library.

name: Festering Goblin
text: When Festering Goblin dies, target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn.
flavor: In life, it was a fetid, disease-ridden thing. In death, not much changed.

name: I Delight in Your Convulsions
text: When you set this scheme in motion, each opponent loses 3 life. You gain life equal to the life lost this way.
flavor: "I can't imagine what you're feeling right now, but I'll try my best."

name: Incremental Blight
text: Put a -1/-1 counter on target creature, two -1/-1 counters on another target creature, and three -1/-1 counters on a third target creature.
flavor: Shadowmoor's main crops are rot, slime, and despair.

name: I Know All, I See All
text: (An ongoing scheme remains face up until it's abandoned.)\nUntap all permanents you control during each opponent's untap step.\nAt the beginning of each end step, if three or more cards were put into your graveyard this turn from anywhere, abandon this scheme.

name: Infectious Horror
text: Whenever Infectious Horror attacks, each opponent loses 2 life.
flavor: Not once in the history of Grixis has anyone died of old age.

name: Ignite the Cloneforge!
text: When you set this scheme in motion, put a token onto the battlefield that's a copy of target permanent an opponent controls.
flavor: "Heroes innovate. Villains duplicate."

name: Infest
text: All creatures get -2/-2 until end of turn.
flavor: "This is why we don't go out in banewasp weather."\n—Rannon, Vithian holdout

name: Into the Earthen Maw
text: When you set this scheme in motion, exile up to one target creature with flying, up to one target creature without flying, and all cards from up to one target opponent's graveyard.
flavor: "You may even see them again. Full digestion takes three hundred years."

name: Makeshift Mannequin
text: Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield with a mannequin counter on it. For as long as that creature has a mannequin counter on it, it has "When this creature becomes the target of a spell or ability, sacrifice it."
flavor: "This vulgar mimicry will end now."\n—Desmera, perfect of Wren's Run

name: Introductions Are in Order
text: When you set this scheme in motion, choose one —\n• Search your library for a creature card, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle your library.\n• You may put a creature card from your hand onto the battlefield.
flavor: "Meet my newest minion. Come now, don't be shy—shake her pincer."

name: Reanimate
text: Put target creature card from a graveyard onto the battlefield under your control. You lose life equal to its converted mana cost.
flavor: "You will learn to earn death."\n—Volrath

name: The Iron Guardian Stirs
text: When you set this scheme in motion, put a 4/6 colorless Golem artifact creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: "It would be disappointing if you were unable to overcome this simplest of defenses. Hilarious, but disappointing."

name: Reassembling Skeleton
text: {1}{B}: Return Reassembling Skeleton from your graveyard to the battlefield tapped.
flavor: Though you may see the same bones, you'll never see the same skeleton twice.

name: Know Naught but Fire
text: When you set this scheme in motion, it deals damage to each opponent equal to the number of cards in that player's hand.
flavor: "Cranial explosions for everyone. Still planning to outthink my dragons?"

name: Scion of Darkness
text: Trample\nWhenever Scion of Darkness deals combat damage to a player, you may put target creature card from that player's graveyard onto the battlefield under your control.\nCycling {3} ({3}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)

name: Look Skyward and Despair
text: When you set this scheme in motion, put a 5/5 red Dragon creature token with flying onto the battlefield.
flavor: "Today I take the reins of destiny itself. Today the Draconic Apocalypse is upon you."

name: Shriekmaw
text: Fear (This creature can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)\nWhen Shriekmaw enters the battlefield, destroy target nonartifact, nonblack creature.\nEvoke {1}{B} (You may cast this spell for its evoke cost. If you do, it's sacrificed when it enters the battlefield.)

name: May Civilization Collapse
text: When you set this scheme in motion, target opponent chooses self or others. If that player chooses self, he or she sacrifices two lands. If the player chooses others, each of your other opponents sacrifices a land.
flavor: "This should halt the spread of your insolence."

name: Sign in Blood
text: Target player draws two cards and loses 2 life.
flavor: "You know I accept only one currency here, and yet you have sought me out. Why now do you hesitate?"\n—Xathrid demon

name: Mortal Flesh Is Weak
text: When you set this scheme in motion, each opponent's life total becomes the lowest life total among your opponents.
flavor: "I certainly would have accepted my offer of eternal life. But if you choose death instead, who am I to argue?"

name: Twisted Abomination
text: {B}: Regenerate Twisted Abomination.\nSwampcycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Search your library for a Swamp card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library.)

name: My Crushing Masterstroke
text: When you set this scheme in motion, gain control of all nonland permanents your opponents control until end of turn. Untap those permanents. They gain haste until end of turn. Each of them attacks its owner this turn if able.

name: Urborg Syphon-Mage
text: {2}{B}, {T}, Discard a card: Each other player loses 2 life. You gain life equal to the life lost this way.
flavor: "I have become a gourmet of sorts. Each soul has its own distinctive flavor. The art is in inviting the right company to the feast."

name: My Genius Knows No Bounds
text: When you set this scheme in motion, you may pay {X}. If you do, you gain X life and draw X cards.
flavor: "I can see . . . everything. The beginning and the end of time. The raw edges of reality. And now I see exactly how to kill you."

name: Zombie Infestation
text: Discard two cards: Put a 2/2 black Zombie creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: The nomads' funeral pyres are more practical than ceremonial.

name: My Undead Horde Awakens
text: (An ongoing scheme remains face up until it's abandoned.)\nAt the beginning of your end step, you may put target creature card from an opponent's graveyard onto the battlefield under your control.\nWhen a creature put onto the battlefield with this scheme dies, abandon this scheme.

name: Zombify
text: Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
flavor: "The first birth celebrates life. The second birth mocks it."\n—Mystic elder

name: My Wish Is Your Command
text: When you set this scheme in motion, each opponent reveals his or her hand. You may choose a noncreature, nonland card revealed this way and cast it without paying its mana cost.
flavor: "Indulge me. Just one spell. One potentially fatal spell gone horribly awry."

name: Battering Craghorn
text: First strike\nMorph {1}{R}{R} (You may cast this card face down as a 2/2 creature for {3}. Turn it face up any time for its morph cost.)
flavor: Their skeletons can be found all over Skirk Ridge, tangled in each other's horns.

name: Nature Demands an Offering
text: When you set this scheme in motion, target opponent chooses a creature you don't control and puts it on top of its owner's library, then repeats this process for an artifact, an enchantment, and a land. Then the owner of each permanent chosen this way shuffles his or her library.

name: Breath of Darigaaz
text: Kicker {2} (You may pay an additional {2} as you cast this spell.)\nBreath of Darigaaz deals 1 damage to each creature without flying and each player. If Breath of Darigaaz was kicked, it deals 4 damage to each creature without flying and each player instead.

name: Nature Shields Its Own
text: (An ongoing scheme remains face up until it's abandoned.)\nWhenever a creature attacks and isn't blocked, if you're the defending player, put a 0/1 green Plant creature token onto the battlefield blocking that creature.\nWhen four or more creatures attack you, abandon this scheme at end of combat.

name: Chandra's Outrage
text: Chandra's Outrage deals 4 damage to target creature and 2 damage to that creature's controller.
flavor: "Her mind is an incredible mix of emotion and power. Even if I could grasp it, I couldn't hold it for long."\n—Jace Beleren, on Chandra Nalaar

name: Nothing Can Stop Me Now
text: (An ongoing scheme remains face up until it's abandoned.)\nIf a source an opponent controls would deal damage to you, prevent 1 of that damage.\nAt the beginning of each end step, if you've been dealt 5 or more damage this turn, abandon this scheme.

name: Dragon Breath
text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature has haste.
{R}: Enchanted creature gets +1/+0 until end of turn.
When a creature with converted mana cost 6 or greater enters the battlefield, you may return Dragon Breath from your graveyard to the battlefield attached to that creature.

name: Only Blood Ends Your Nightmares
text: When you set this scheme in motion, each opponent sacrifices a creature. Then each opponent who didn't sacrifice a creature discards two cards.
flavor: "But nothing will end your regret."

name: Dragon Fodder
text: Put two 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: Goblins journey to the sacrificial peaks in pairs so that the rare survivor might be able to relate the details of the other's grisly demise.

name: The Pieces Are Coming Together
text: When you set this scheme in motion, draw two cards. Artifact spells you cast this turn cost {2} less to cast.
flavor: "Cretins build machines. I construct destiny."

name: Dragon Whelp
text: Flying\n{R}: Dragon Whelp gets +1/+0 until end of turn. If this ability has been activated four or more times this turn, sacrifice Dragon Whelp at the beginning of the next end step.

name: Realms Befitting My Majesty
text: When you set this scheme in motion, search your library for up to two basic land cards, put them onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle your library.
flavor: "Look around you. All you behold is mine to rule. It's the natural way."

name: Dragonspeaker Shaman
text: Dragon spells you cast cost {2} less to cast.
flavor: "We speak the dragons' language of flame and rage. They speak our language of fury and honor. Together we shall weave a tale of destruction without equal."

name: Roots of All Evil
text: When you set this scheme in motion, put five 1/1 green Saproling creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: "I assure you, these are not the kind that thrive on sunlight and water."

name: Fireball
text: Fireball deals X damage divided evenly, rounded down, among any number of target creatures and/or players.\nFireball costs {1} more to cast for each target beyond the first.

name: Rotted Ones, Lay Siege
text: When you set this scheme in motion, for each opponent, put a 2/2 black Zombie creature token onto the battlefield that attacks that player each combat if able.
flavor: "Don't come back until you've got brains in your teeth."

name: Flameblast Dragon
text: Flying\nWhenever Flameblast Dragon attacks, you may pay {X}{R}. If you do, Flameblast Dragon deals X damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Dragon lords of Jund rule by edicts of flame.

name: Surrender Your Thoughts
text: When you set this scheme in motion, target opponent chooses self or others. If that player chooses self, he or she discards four cards. If the player chooses others, each of your other opponents discards two cards.
flavor: "Or, if you prefer, just surrender."

name: Furnace Whelp
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\n{R}: Furnace Whelp gets +1/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: Baby dragons can't figure out humans—if they didn't want to be killed, why were they made of meat and treasure?

name: Tooth, Claw, and Tail
text: When you set this scheme in motion, destroy up to three target nonland permanents.
flavor: "Silence your wailing. This is but a taste of the destruction my pets have in store."

name: Gathan Raiders
text: Hellbent — Gathan Raiders gets +2/+2 as long as you have no cards in hand.\nMorph—Discard a card. (You may cast this card face down as a 2/2 creature for {3}. Turn it face up any time for its morph cost.)

name: The Very Soil Shall Shake
text: (An ongoing scheme remains face up until it's abandoned.)\nCreatures you control get +2/+2 and have trample.\nWhen a creature you control dies, abandon this scheme.

name: Hellkite Charger
text: Flying, haste\nWhenever Hellkite Charger attacks, you may pay {5}{R}{R}. If you do, untap all attacking creatures and after this phase, there is an additional combat phase.

name: Which of You Burns Brightest?
text: When you set this scheme in motion, you may pay {X}. If you do, this scheme deals X damage to target opponent and each creature he or she controls.
flavor: "Let that be a lesson to you, your family, and everyone you've ever known."

name: Imperial Hellkite
text: Flying\nMorph {6}{R}{R} (You may cast this card face down as a 2/2 creature for {3}. Turn it face up any time for its morph cost.)\nWhen Imperial Hellkite is turned face up, you may search your library for a Dragon card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. If you do, shuffle your library.

name: Your Fate Is Thrice Sealed
text: When you set this scheme in motion, reveal the top three cards of your library. Put all land cards revealed this way onto the battlefield and the rest into your hand.
flavor: "I can't abide laziness. Arise, forces of nature, and serve your master!"

name: Inferno Trap
text: If you've been dealt damage by two or more creatures this turn, you may pay {R} rather than pay Inferno Trap's mana cost.\nInferno Trap deals 4 damage to target creature.
flavor: "Do you smell something burning?"

name: Your Puny Minds Cannot Fathom
text: When you set this scheme in motion, draw four cards. You have no maximum hand size until your next turn.
flavor: "I have seen far beyond this imperfect world, into a tomorrow that doesn't include you."

name: Kilnmouth Dragon
text: Amplify 3 (As this creature enters the battlefield, put three +1/+1 counters on it for each Dragon card you reveal in your hand.)\nFlying\n{T}: Kilnmouth Dragon deals damage equal to the number of +1/+1 counters on it to target creature or player.

name: Your Will Is Not Your Own
text: When you set this scheme in motion, gain control of target creature an opponent controls until end of turn. Untap that creature. It gets +3/+3 and gains trample and haste until end of turn.
flavor: "Fool. I'll show you how to use that thing."

name: Ryusei, the Falling Star
text: Flying\nWhen Ryusei, the Falling Star dies, it deals 5 damage to each creature without flying.

name: Seething Song
text: Add {R}{R}{R}{R}{R} to your mana pool.
flavor: Vulshok mana rituals echo the day when the red sun burst through Mirrodin's surface to take its place in the heavens.

name: Skirk Commando
text: Whenever Skirk Commando deals combat damage to a player, you may have it deal 2 damage to target creature that player controls.\nMorph {2}{R} (You may cast this card face down as a 2/2 creature for {3}. Turn it face up any time for its morph cost.)

name: Skirk Marauder
text: Morph {2}{R} (You may cast this card face down as a 2/2 creature for {3}. Turn it face up any time for its morph cost.)\nWhen Skirk Marauder is turned face up, it deals 2 damage to target creature or player.

name: Taurean Mauler
text: Changeling (This card is every creature type.)\nWhenever an opponent casts a spell, you may put a +1/+1 counter on Taurean Mauler.
flavor: The power of a waterfall. The fury of an avalanche. The intellect of a gale-force wind.

name: Two-Headed Dragon
text:
Flying
Menace (This creature can't be blocked except by two or more creatures.)
Two-Headed Dragon can block an additional creature each combat.
{1}{R}: Two-Headed Dragon gets +2/+0 until end of turn.

name: Volcanic Fallout
text: Volcanic Fallout can't be countered.\nVolcanic Fallout deals 2 damage to each creature and each player.
flavor: "How can we outrun the sky?"\n—Hadran, sunseeder of Naya

name: Chameleon Colossus
text: Changeling (This card is every creature type.)\nProtection from black\n{2}{G}{G}: Chameleon Colossus gets +X/+X until end of turn, where X is its power.

name: Feral Hydra
text: Feral Hydra enters the battlefield with X +1/+1 counters on it.\n{3}: Put a +1/+1 counter on Feral Hydra. Any player may activate this ability.
flavor: It shreds its prey as each head fights for the choicest bits.

name: Fertilid
text: Fertilid enters the battlefield with two +1/+1 counters on it.\n{1}{G}, Remove a +1/+1 counter from Fertilid: Target player searches his or her library for a basic land card and puts it onto the battlefield tapped. Then that player shuffles his or her library.

name: Fierce Empath
text: When Fierce Empath enters the battlefield, you may search your library for a creature card with converted mana cost 6 or greater, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle your library.

name: Fog
text: Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt this turn.
flavor: "I fear no army or beast, but only the morning fog. Our assault can survive everything else."\n—Lord Hilneth

name: Forgotten Ancient
text: Whenever a player casts a spell, you may put a +1/+1 counter on Forgotten Ancient.\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, you may move any number of +1/+1 counters from Forgotten Ancient onto other creatures.
flavor: Its blood is life. Its body is growth.

name: Gleeful Sabotage
text: Destroy target artifact or enchantment.\nConspire (As you cast this spell, you may tap two untapped creatures you control that share a color with it. When you do, copy it and you may choose a new target for the copy.)

name: Harmonize
text: Draw three cards.
flavor: "Words lie. People lie. The land tells the truth."

name: Hunting Moa
text: Echo {2}{G} (At the beginning of your upkeep, if this came under your control since the beginning of your last upkeep, sacrifice it unless you pay its echo cost.)\nWhen Hunting Moa enters the battlefield or dies, put a +1/+1 counter on target creature.

name: Kamahl, Fist of Krosa
text: {G}: Target land becomes a 1/1 creature until end of turn. It's still a land.\n{2}{G}{G}{G}: Creatures you control get +3/+3 and gain trample until end of turn.
flavor: "My mind has changed. My strength has not."

name: Krosan Tusker
text: Cycling {2}{G} ({2}{G}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)\nWhen you cycle Krosan Tusker, you may search your library for a basic land card, reveal that card, put it into your hand, then shuffle your library.

name: Leaf Gilder
text: {T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.
flavor: Eidren, perfect of Lys Alana, ordered hundreds of trees uprooted and rearranged into a pattern he deemed beautiful. Thus the Gilt-Leaf Wood was born.

name: Molimo, Maro-Sorcerer
text: Trample (This creature can deal excess combat damage to defending player or planeswalker while attacking.)\nMolimo, Maro-Sorcerer's power and toughness are each equal to the number of lands you control.
flavor: "My mind is the spread of the canopy. My heart is the embrace of the roots. I am deathless Llanowar, its fury and its peace."

name: Plummet
text: Destroy target creature with flying.
flavor: "You are the grandest of all," said the archdruid to the trees. They became so proud of bark and branch that they suffered no creature to fly overhead or perch upon a bough.

name: Primal Command
text:
Choose two —
• Target player gains 7 life.
• Put target noncreature permanent on top of its owner's library.
• Target player shuffles his or her graveyard into his or her library.
• Search your library for a creature card, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle your library.

name: Rancor
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/+0 and has trample.\nWhen Rancor is put into a graveyard from the battlefield, return Rancor to its owner's hand.
flavor: Hatred outlives the hateful.

name: Sakura-Tribe Elder
text: Sacrifice Sakura-Tribe Elder: Search your library for a basic land card, put that card onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle your library.
flavor: Slain orochi warriors were buried with a tree sapling so they would become a part of the forest after death.

name: Shinen of Life's Roar
text: All creatures able to block Shinen of Life's Roar do so.\nChannel — {2}{G}{G}, Discard Shinen of Life's Roar: All creatures able to block target creature this turn do so.

name: Spider Umbra
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +1/+1 and has reach. (It can block creatures with flying.)\nTotem armor (If enchanted creature would be destroyed, instead remove all damage from it and destroy this Aura.)

name: Thelonite Hermit
text: Saproling creatures get +1/+1.\nMorph {3}{G}{G} (You may cast this card face down as a 2/2 creature for {3}. Turn it face up any time for its morph cost.)\nWhen Thelonite Hermit is turned face up, put four 1/1 green Saproling creature tokens onto the battlefield.

name: Verdeloth the Ancient
text: Kicker {X} (You may pay an additional {X} as you cast this spell.)\nSaproling creatures and other Treefolk creatures get +1/+1.\nWhen Verdeloth the Ancient enters the battlefield, if it was kicked, put X 1/1 green Saproling creature tokens onto the battlefield.

name: Wall of Roots
text: Defender\nPut a -0/-1 counter on Wall of Roots: Add {G} to your mana pool. Activate this ability only once each turn.
flavor: Sometimes the wise ones wove their magic into living plants; as the plant grew, so grew the magic.

name: Wickerbough Elder
text: Wickerbough Elder enters the battlefield with a -1/-1 counter on it.\n{G}, Remove a -1/-1 counter from Wickerbough Elder: Destroy target artifact or enchantment.
flavor: "Living scarecrows make a mockery of the natural order. Dead ones make fine hats."

name: Yavimaya Dryad

name: Agony Warp
text: Target creature gets -3/-0 until end of turn.\nTarget creature gets -0/-3 until end of turn.
flavor: Life's circle has become inverted in Grixis. The same energy is endlessly recycled and becomes more stagnant with each pass.

flavor: This secret society of mages manipulates the beliefs and opinions of others.

name: Armadillo Cloak
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/+2 and has trample.\nWhenever enchanted creature deals damage, you gain that much life.

text: ({B/R} can be paid with either {B} or {R}.)\nFlying\nWhen Avatar of Discord enters the battlefield, sacrifice it unless you discard two cards.
flavor: Such is the power of Rakdos that even his shadow takes on a cruel life of its own.

name: Batwing Brume

name: Bituminous Blast

name: Branching Bolt

name: Colossal Might
text: Target creature gets +4/+2 and gains trample until end of turn.
flavor: "Never corner a barbarian. You become the path of least resistance."\n—Sarkhan Vol

name: Ethersworn Shieldmage

name: Heroes' Reunion
text: Target player gains 7 life.
flavor: "You helped save my people from a Phyrexian fate. Did you think I wouldn't return the favor?"\n—Eladamri, to Gerrard

name: Magister Sphinx
text: Flying\nWhen Magister Sphinx enters the battlefield, target player's life total becomes 10.
flavor: "These benighted worlds are thick with ignorance. I will educate them. They will listen, or they will die."

text: You may pay {1} and return a basic land you control to its owner's hand rather than pay Mistvein Borderpost's mana cost.\nMistvein Borderpost enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {U} or {B} to your mana pool.

text: ({B/R} can be paid with either {B} or {R}.)\n{3}{B}, Discard a card: Target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn.\n{3}{R}: Put a 2/1 red Goblin creature token with haste onto the battlefield. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step.

name: Savage Twister

name: Selesnya Guildmage

name: Terminate
text: Destroy target creature. It can't be regenerated.
flavor: "I've seen death before. My mother succumbing to illness, my comrades bleeding on the battlefield . . . But I'd never seen anything as dreadful as that."\n—Taani, berserker of Etlan

name: Torrent of Souls

name: Unbender Tine
text: {T}: Untap another target permanent.
flavor: Creations made in madness may contain great power. The path to that power is as labyrinthine as the creator's mind.

name: Unmake
text: Exile target creature.
flavor: A gwyllion's favorite trap is the vanity mirror. A bewitched piece of glass traps the looker's soul and does away with the body.

name: Watchwolf

text: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn.

name: Azorius Signet

name: Dimir Signet
text: {1}, {T}: Add {U}{B} to your mana pool.

flavor: Only the Eldrazi mind thinks in the warped paths required to open the hedrons and tap the power within.

name: Duplicant

name: Gruul Signet
text: {1}, {T}: Add {R}{G} to your mana pool.
flavor: Gruul territorial markings need not be legible. The blood, snot, and muck used to smear them are unmistakably Gruul.

name: Juggernaut
text: Juggernaut attacks each turn if able.\nJuggernaut can't be blocked by Walls.
flavor: Built with neither a way to steer nor a way to stop, the juggernauts were simply aimed at an enemy's best defenses and told to charge.

name: Lightning Greaves
text: Equipped creature has haste and shroud. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities.)\nEquip {0}
flavor: After lightning struck the cliffs, the ore became iron, the iron became steel, and the steel became greaves. The lightning never left.

name: Lodestone Golem

flavor: In the blur between metal and flesh, Memnarch found madness.

name: Obelisk of Esper

name: Rakdos Signet
text: {1}, {T}: Add {B}{R} to your mana pool.
flavor: Made of bone and boiled in blood, a Rakdos signet is not considered finished until it has been used as a murder weapon.

name: Skullcage

flavor: Only a focused mind can survive it.

name: Sorcerer's Strongbox
text: {2}, {T}: Flip a coin. If you win the flip, sacrifice Sorcerer's Strongbox and draw three cards.
flavor: Simun the Quiet filled the chest with his most precious thoughts. But in a fit of paranoia, he locked up the memory of where he hid the key.

name: Sun Droplet

name: Sundering Titan

name: Synod Centurion
